    <br>
    <b>WORD 1: "<b><i>the</i>"</b>
    <br>
    <br>
    Spanish: la (feminine)   /  el (masculine)
    <br>
    Italian:  la (feminine)      /  il (masculine)
    <br>
    French: les / la / le
    <br>
    German: die / den / der / das
    <br>
    Chinese: 该  Gāi
    <br>
    <br>
    WORD 2: "<b><i>of</i>"</<b>
    <br>
    <br>
    Spanish: de
    <br>
    Italian: di
    <br>
    French: de
    <br>
    German: von
    <br>
    Chinese: 的 (De)
    <br>
    <br>
    WORD 3: "<b><i>and</i>"</<b>
    <br>
    <br>
    Spanish: y
    <br>
    Italian: e
    <br>
    French: et
    <br>
    German: und
    <br>
    Chinese: 和 (Hé)
    <br>

    <br>
    WORD 4: "<b><i>a</i>"</<b>
    <br>
    <br>
    Spanish: un (masculine) / una (feminine)
    <br>
    Italian:  un (masculine) / una (feminine)
    <br>
    French:  un (masculine) / une (feminine)
    <br>
    German: ein / eine
    <br>
    Chinese: 一个 (Yīgè)
    <br>
    <br>
    WORD 5: "<b><i>to</i>"</<b>
    <br>
    <br>
    Spanish: a
    <br>
    Italian: a
    <br>
    French: à
    <br>
    German: zu
    <br>
    Chinese: 至 (Zhì)
    <br>

