<h3>Here are some fun facts about languages!</h3>
<ol>
	<li> South Africa has the most official languages with 11. </li>
	<li> The English language contains the most words, with over 250,000. </li>
	<li> Russian was the first language spoken in outer space. </li>
	<li> People who speak and understand Chinese use both sides of the brain, whereas English only uses the left side. </li>
	<li> Multiple studies have shown that learning a second language can improve the memory and slow the process of aging. </li>
<ol>




